==.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all dart-core.Objects is to return true if and only if this and pixelate/pixelate_scroll_viewer.HtmlElement+Polymer+Observable.==.other are the same object.

Override this method to specify a different equality relation on a class. The overriding method must still be an equivalence relation. That is, it must be:

  • Total: It must return a boolean for all arguments. It should never throw or return null.

  • Reflexive: For all objects o, o == o must be true.

  • Symmetric: For all objects o1 and o2, o1 == o2 and o2 == o1 must either both be true, or both be false.

  • Transitive: For all objects o1, o2, and o3, if o1 == o2 and o2 == o3 are true, then o1 == o3 must be true.

The method should also be consistent over time, so equality of two objects should not change over time, or at least only change if one of the objects was modified.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override the pixelate/pixelate_scroll_viewer.HtmlElement+Polymer+Observable.hashCode method as well to maintain consistency.

This is identical to pixelate/pixelate_scroll_viewer.Element.shadowRoot, unless there are multiple levels of inheritance and they each have their own shadow root. For example, this can happen if the base class and subclass both have <template> tags in their <polymer-element> tags.

polymerCreated.name: polymerCreated
polymerCreated.comment:
If this class is used as a mixin, this method must be called from inside of the created() constructor.

If this class is a superclass, calling super.created() is sufficient.

parseDeclaration.name: parseDeclaration
parseDeclaration.comment: Parse input <polymer-element> as needed, override for custom behavior.

fetchTemplate.name: fetchTemplate
fetchTemplate.comment: Return a shadow-root template (if desired), override for custom behavior.

lightFromTemplate.name: lightFromTemplate
lightFromTemplate.comment: Utility function that stamps a <template> into light-dom.

shadowFromTemplate.name: shadowFromTemplate
shadowFromTemplate.comment:
Utility function that creates a shadow root from a <template>.

The base implementation will return a pixelate/dart-dom-html.ShadowRoot, but you can replace it with your own code and skip ShadowRoot creation. In that case, you should return null.

In your overridden method, you can use pixelate/pixelate_scroll_viewer.HtmlElement+Polymer+Observable.instanceTemplate to stamp the template and initialize data binding, and pixelate/pixelate_scroll_viewer.HtmlElement+Polymer+Observable.shadowRootReady to intialize other Polymer features like event handlers. It is fine to call shadowRootReady with a node other than a ShadowRoot such as with this.

marshalNodeReferences.name: marshalNodeReferences
marshalNodeReferences.comment: Locate nodes with id and store references to them in pixelate/polymer.Polymer.$ hash.

onMutation.name: onMutation
onMutation.comment:
Returns a future when node changes, or when its children or subtree changes.

Use pixelate/dart-dom-html.MutationObserver if you want to listen to a stream of changes.

attributeToProperty.name: attributeToProperty
attributeToProperty.comment: If attribute pixelate/pixelate_scroll_viewer.HtmlElement+Polymer+Observable.attributeToProperty.name is mapped to a property, deserialize pixelate/pixelate_scroll_viewer.HtmlElement+Polymer+Observable.attributeToProperty.value into that property.

propertyForAttribute.name: propertyForAttribute
propertyForAttribute.comment: Return the published property matching name, or null.

instanceTemplate.name: instanceTemplate
instanceTemplate.comment:
Creates the document fragment to use for each instance of the custom element, given the <template> node. By default this is equivalent to:

templateBind(template).createInstance(this, polymerSyntax);

Where polymerSyntax is a singleton PolymerExpressions instance from the polymer_expressions package.

You can override this method to change the instantiation behavior of the template, for example to use a different data-binding syntax.

notifyPropertyChanges.name: notifyPropertyChanges
notifyPropertyChanges.comment: Responds to property changes on this element.

bindProperty.name: bindProperty
bindProperty.comment:
Bind a property in this object to a path in model. Note in Dart it is necessary to also define the field:

var myProperty;

ready() {
  super.ready();
  bindProperty(#myProperty, this, 'myModel.path.to.otherProp');
}

addHostListeners.name: addHostListeners
addHostListeners.comment: Attach event listeners on the host (this) element.

dispatchMethod.name: dispatchMethod
dispatchMethod.comment: Calls methodOrCallback with pixelate/pixelate_scroll_viewer.HtmlElement+Polymer+Observable.dispatchMethod.args if it is a closure, otherwise, treat it as a method name in pixelate/pixelate_scroll_viewer.HtmlElement+Polymer+Observable.dispatchMethod.object, and invoke it.

asyncTimer.name: asyncTimer
asyncTimer.comment:
Invokes a function asynchronously. This will call Platform.flush() and then return a new Timer with the provided pixelate/pixelate_scroll_viewer.HtmlElement+Polymer+Observable.asyncTimer.method and pixelate/pixelate_scroll_viewer.HtmlElement+Polymer+Observable.asyncTimer.timeout.

If you would prefer to run the callback using window.requestAnimationFrame, see the pixelate/pixelate_scroll_viewer.HtmlElement+Polymer+Observable.async method.

async.name: async
async.comment:
Invokes a function asynchronously. This will call Platform.flush() and then call window.requestAnimationFrame with the provided pixelate/pixelate_scroll_viewer.HtmlElement+Polymer+Observable.async.method and return the result.

If you would prefer to run the callback after a given duration, see the pixelate/pixelate_scroll_viewer.HtmlElement+Polymer+Observable.asyncTimer method.

fire.name: fire
fire.comment: Fire a pixelate/dart-dom-html.CustomEvent targeting pixelate/pixelate_scroll_viewer.HtmlElement+Polymer+Observable.fire.toNode, or this if toNode is not supplied. Returns the pixelate/pixelate_scroll_viewer.HtmlElement+Polymer+Observable.fire.detail object.

classFollows.name: classFollows
classFollows.comment: Remove pixelate/pixelate_scroll_viewer.HtmlElement+Polymer+Observable.classFollows.className from pixelate/pixelate_scroll_viewer.HtmlElement+Polymer+Observable.classFollows.old, add class to pixelate/pixelate_scroll_viewer.HtmlElement+Polymer+Observable.classFollows.anew, if they exist.

installControllerStyles.name: installControllerStyles
installControllerStyles.comment:
Installs external stylesheets and <style> elements with the attribute polymer-scope='controller' into the scope of element. This is intended to be a called during custom element construction. Note, this incurs a per instance cost and should be used sparingly.

The need for this type of styling should go away when the shadowDOM spec addresses these issues:

https://www.w3.org/Bugs/Public/showbug.cgi?id=21391 https://www.w3.org/Bugs/Public/showbug.cgi?id=21390 https://www.w3.org/Bugs/Public/show_bug.cgi?id=21389

@param element The custom element instance into whose controller (parent) scope styles will be installed. @param elementElement The <element> containing controller styles.
